Two Russian missile strikes hit the main television tower in the heart of the Kyiv on Tuesday afternoon, killing five civilans and injuring more. Dramatic smoke was seen rising from the tower, although the structure of the tower is thought to still be intact. The TV tower is in the vicinity of Babi Yar, a ravine where Nazi's killed 33,000 people in one of the worst mass killings of the Holocaust. Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky said on Twitter that history was "repeating" itself, asking: "To the world: what is the point of saying never again for 80 years, if the world stays silent when a bomb drops on the same site of Babyn Yar?" FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES...